      "description": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) predictions from the CFD model were compared against a high-fidelity reference numerical simulation of the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Agreement within 8% across all 5 flow-speed operating points was interpreted as confirming model predictive validity. The analysis team noted that the reference simulation employs validated turbulence closure and fine mesh resolution, arguing it constitutes an equivalent evidentiary basis to a physical experiment for the purpose of hemolysis index comparison.",
